reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on December 2, 2023
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Fits Lopi AGP for aa fraction of the cost
reviews.reviewText: I have a 10 year old Lopi AGP pellet stove, when the igniter went out, the local dealer wanted over three hundred for a new one … I’m cheep, so I took the old one apart and started a search, the Englander 350 watt element is the perfect fit after doing a mod that anyone handy can do. Remove the collar with an Allen wrench and swap out the connectors for the correct ones, remove the Lopi element from the old igniter housing with an Allen wrench, slide in the new element and lock down the Allen screw, re install the igniter into the stove, works like brand new and cost only 15 bucks!
